HEADWORD: Miterwort
<hw>Mi"ter*wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Any plant of the genus <gen>Mitella</gen>, -- slender, perennial
herbs with a pod slightly resembling a bishop's miter; bishop's
cap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>False miterwort</b></col>, <cd>a white-flowered perennial
herb of the United States (<spn>Tiarella
cardifolia</spn>).</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mithic</ent>⟦br⟧
